<subSubSection id="C31C65001988FF4F6A8BA3927261FBF6" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1988FF4F6A8BA39271E5FB9B" blockId="168.[189,457,1013,1039]" box="[189,457,1013,1039]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">
<heading id="D0F181E71988FF4F6A8BA39271E5FB9B" bold="true" box="[189,457,1013,1039]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B972EA991988FF4F6A8BA39271E5FB9B" bold="true" box="[189,457,1013,1039]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1988FF4F6A8BA4437261FBF6" blockId="168.[189,1398,1060,1122]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">
This species is not very similar to any described species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D081988FF4F6947A44373F2FBAA" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[881,990,1060,1086]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B972EA991988FF4F6947A44373F2FBAA" box="[881,990,1060,1086]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Sphegina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and should be easily distinguished by the characters given in the key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31C65001988FF4F6A8BA4ED7252FB6C" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1988FF4F6A8BA4ED7168FB30" blockId="168.[189,324,1162,1188]" box="[189,324,1162,1188]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">
<heading id="D0F181E71988FF4F6A8BA4ED7168FB30" bold="true" box="[189,324,1162,1188]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B972EA991988FF4F6A8BA4ED7168FB30" bold="true" box="[189,324,1162,1188]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1988FF4F6A8BA4DD7252FB6C" blockId="168.[189,1399,1210,1272]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D081988FF4F684BA4DD72DDFB40" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[637,753,1210,1236]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigillata">
<emphasis id="B972EA991988FF4F684BA4DD72DDFB40" box="[637,753,1210,1236]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">strigillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning ‘with a scraper’ and referring to the scraperlike posterior part of male sternum IV.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
