HEAD. Face in lateral view, 
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E1988FF4F683FA6B3725FF97A" box="[521,627,1748,1774]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="170.[189,232,1821,1847]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,457,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@170.[189,1399,457,1781]" captionTargetPageId="170" captionText="Fig. 88. Head. lateral view (C, E, F, J) and dorsal view (A–B, D, G–I, K–L). A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) spathigera sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Philippines. B–C. S. (A.) spenceri sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Vietnam. D–E. S. (A.) strigillata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Vietnam. F. S. (A.) tricoloripes, Brunetti, 1915, ♀, India. G. S. (A.) tricoloripes, Ƌ, India. H. S. (A.) umbrosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. I. S. (A.) varidissima Shiraki, 1930, Ƌ, Taiwan. J. S. (A.) varidissima, ♀, Taiwan. K. S. (A.) verrucosa sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Vietnam. L. S. (A.) vietnamensis sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Vietnam. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830732" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830732/files/figure.png" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Fig. 88E</figureCitation>
, concave, weakly projected antero-ventrally; frontal prominence strongly developed. Ratio width of vertex at anterior ocellus: width of head 1: 3.5–3.7; ratio width of ocellar triangle: width of vertex 1: 1.9–2.1; ratio length of ocellar triangle: length of frons 1: 1.8– 2.1. Face black, light grey pollinose, long pilose along eye-margin. Hypostomal bridge black, long pale pilose. Gena and mouth edge dark brown, pale pollinose with large subtriangular non-pollinose shiny area. Frons and vertex black, large rectangular vitta posterior of lunula non-pollinose and shiny (
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E1988FF4F6AF0A7CC7119F851" box="[198,309,1963,1989]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="170.[189,232,1821,1847]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,457,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@170.[189,1399,457,1781]" captionTargetPageId="170" captionText="Fig. 88. Head. lateral view (C, E, F, J) and dorsal view (A–B, D, G–I, K–L). A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) spathigera sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Philippines. B–C. S. (A.) spenceri sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Vietnam. D–E. S. (A.) strigillata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Vietnam. F. S. (A.) tricoloripes, Brunetti, 1915, ♀, India. G. S. (A.) tricoloripes, Ƌ, India. H. S. (A.) umbrosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. I. S. (A.) varidissima Shiraki, 1930, Ƌ, Taiwan. J. S. (A.) varidissima, ♀, Taiwan. K. S. (A.) verrucosa sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Vietnam. L. S. (A.) vietnamensis sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Vietnam. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830732" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830732/files/figure.png" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Fig. 88D</figureCitation>
); pile short, light yellow. Frons with very weak and narrow medial furrow. Occiput black, light grey pollinose, light yellow pilose. Eye without enlarged facets at anterior margin. Antenna brown- yellow with black setae dorsally on scape and pedicel; basoflagellomere oval, ratio width: length 1: 1.2–1.4; arista long pilose, about 3.5 times as long as basoflagellomere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1989FF4E6A8BA10974C2FE66" blockId="169.[189,1399,366,498]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">THORAX. Colour dark brown to black, weakly greyish pollinose, scutum with densely grey pollinose vitta submedially, pleuron entirely grey pollinose; scutum and pleuron with very short adpressed light yellow pile. Scutellum sub-triangular, black, shiny, with pile slightly longer than on scutum, with two widely set short setae medially at posterior margin, ratio length of scutellum: length of seta 1: 1.1–1.4.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1989FF4E6A8BA27E70FDFDEE" blockId="169.[189,1399,537,634]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">WING. Entirely microtrichose, hyaline, stigma yellowish, membrane brown infuscated at junction of veins R2+3 and R4+5, along veins bm-cu, r-m, dm-cu and M1, and at medial and apical appendices of vein R</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1989FF4E6AE7A21470C0FD15" box="[209,236,627,641]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">2+3</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1989FF4E6ADDA20773E3FDEE" blockId="169.[189,1399,537,634]" box="[235,975,608,634]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">. Crossvein dm-cu meeting vein M perpendicularly and vein M</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1989FF4E69F9A21473F4FD15" box="[975,984,627,641]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">1</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1989FF4E69E9A20774BFFDEE" blockId="169.[189,1399,537,634]" box="[991,1171,608,634]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">meeting vein R</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1989FF4E6EA4A2147481FD15" box="[1170,1197,627,641]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">4+5</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1989FF4D6E82A207755BFEFE" blockId="169.[189,1399,537,634]" lastBlockId="170.[189,1399,266,362]" lastPageId="170" lastPageNumber="171" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">
perpendicularly. LEGS. Pro- and mesofemur yellow, baso-medial ¼–½ black; pro- and mesotibia yellow, apico-medial 1/5–¼ black; pro- and mesotarsus yellow, tarsomeres 3–5 brown to black. Metaleg, 
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E198AFF4D6EBBA14A74DBFED3" box="[1165,1271,301,327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="185.[189,232,1891,1917]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,743,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@185.[189,1399,743,1852]" captionTargetPageId="185" captionText="Fig. 95. Metaleg, anterior view. A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) plautus sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. B. S. (A.) setosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Nepal. C. S. (A.) strigillata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Vietnam. D. S. (A.) umbrosa sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. E. S. (A.) varidissima Shiraki, 1930, Ƌ, Taiwan, yellow form. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830756/files/figure.png" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Fig. 95C</figureCitation>
, with coxa and trochanter black; femur black and yellow biannulate, incrassate, ratio width: length 1: 3.8–4.0; tibia
</paragraph>
